## Performance Considerations

### CPU Usage Optimization
- ROI selection reduces analysis area
- Increased blur kernel size speeds up processing
- Higher MIN_CONTOUR_AREA reduces contour calculations
- CLI mode has lower overhead than GUI

### Memory Usage
- Default frame size from camera
- Snapshot storage in file system
- Keep snapshots folder cleaned periodically

### Recommended Settings by Use Case

#### Office/Indoor
- Threshold: 20-30
- Min Area: 300-500 pixels
- Good lighting recommended

#### Home Security
- Threshold: 15-25
- Min Area: 300-700 pixels
- Works day and night

#### Warehouse
- Threshold: 25-40
- Min Area: 1000-2000 pixels
- Large areas require larger thresholds

#### Low-Light Environments
- Threshold: 10-20
- Min Area: 200-500 pixels
- May need IR camera for 24/7 operation

## Common Issues & Solutions

### Camera Detection
- Verify camera permissions (especially on Linux)
- Try different CAMERA_ID values (0, 1, -1)
- Test camera with other applications first

### False Positives
- Increase THRESHOLD_VALUE
- Increase MIN_CONTOUR_AREA
- Use ROI to exclude problematic areas
- Improve lighting to reduce noise

### Motion Not Detected
- Decrease THRESHOLD_VALUE
- Decrease MIN_CONTOUR_AREA
- Ensure adequate lighting
- Check camera field of view

### Performance Issues
- Use CLI mode instead of GUI
- Apply ROI selection
- Reduce camera resolution
- Close other applications

